caption: Wow, fantastic place for brunch.  I had seen pictures of the Ube waffle and pancakes and had to make a trip to this restaurant.  So glad we did.  Four people, ordered six meals.  Chicken & waffles were delicious, the pancakes so good.  Not sure what their secret is with the texture of the pancakes, but it’s a winner.  Slightly crisp on outside.  With the delicious coconut you really don’t need the syrup at all.  The red fish was beautifully done and the other dish was a fried rice egg combo. Didn’t catch the name of that.  We were all very happy.  I’ll come back for sure.
We traveled from Indiana to eat here and is very good!!! Salamat Po!!!

My folks grew up in the Philippines, and the pancit bihon tastes just like it did at home. Whenever friends say they've never really tried Flipino food, I bring them here. Standard dishes ordered (family style, the only way at an Asian restaurant): lumpia, lechon, sissig, papaya salad, chicken adobo, and save room for the Halo-Halo.  If you like brunch and fusion food, chef Clarice is good for that too. AND great bartenders/servers who make tasty cocktails and serve delicious food.
(Translated by Google) A patio with space.  (Original) Un patio con espacio..
Surely a place worth stopping by, the food is good and fresh, the prices are convenient and it is always well kept here. Keep it up.
This spot is worth visiting. They serve large portions for reasonable prices. Regularly well organized and with awesome vibes. Would recommend to others.
Love the food here and they have an excellent menu selection too. I do recommend ordering, easy pick up!
The dishes taste very different than other Asian food. Very interesting experience

This spot is the one I like best. I visit plenty of restaurants but to this one I keep coming back again and again. The crew is very helpful and the cuisine they place on your table is so yummy. I never decline to have a decent dinner in this place. I highly recommend this place.

On Valentine's Day, we decided to have dinner at Purple Patch, a Filipino restaurant that also serves American Comfort Food. During this pandemic, you have to go to their market to be seated at their patio, which is first come, first serve. Their market sells blankets, hand knits, wines, beers, fresh flowers, Filipino snacks, and a wide array of desserts. I couldn't walk out without buying Corn and Rice Pudding, Potato Chip and Blue Chocolate Cookies, and Ube Cupcakes. The outdoor patio had infrared heaters. They offer complimentary hand warmers and hand sanitizer.  We weren't impressed with the craft cocktails (e.g., Campfire Crush and Spicy Calamansi Margarita) we ordered. The Campfire Crush consisted of rye, peychaud's bitters, lemon, and smoky ginger ale shaken, served over the rocks, and garnished with a rosemary sprig. I didn't like the flavor nor the bitter aftertaste.  For appetizers, we shared a Cantaloupe Salad, which consisted of cantaloupe topped with shredded snow peas and sliced red onions tossed in a light ginger soy dressing. It was refreshing and spring like.  For entrees, I got to the try the 25oz Bone-In Braised Short Rib Bistek and Maitake Adobo. The 25oz Bone-In Braised Short Rib Bistek consisted of a soy sauce and calamansi braised bone in short rib served with sauteed onions and potatoes, house salad with lemon vinaigrette, crispy onion rings, and a side of garlic fries. The meat was tender, juicy, quite flavor, and slid off  the bone. The Maitake Adobo consisted maitake mushroom, carrots, and zucchini roasted in coconut milk, soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, and bay leaves. It was delicious. However, it would have been nice to serve it with a bowl of jasmine rice.  For dessert, I got to try their Flourless Chocolate Cake with Fresh Strawberries and Ube Bread Pudding with Ube Ice Cream & Caramel with Sparkling Wine. The Flourless Chocolate Cake was sinful. The Ube Bread Pudding was to die for.
Definitely a place worth stopping by, the food is great and well prepared, the pricing is convenient and it is always well organized there. Keep up the good work.

The food was amazing. Jose is a fantastic server, and helped us figure out what we wanted to order since we aren’t familiar with Filipino food. He had a great attitude and was excited to share his knowledge.  Each person thoroughly enjoyed their meal. Esprecially recommend the ube bread pudding. Yummmmmm!!!  Each table had its own space heater. Lots of outdoor seating. Good music too :)
Food is good, bu they didn’t put spoon and fork in my delivery.
I absolutely love the food and service, awesome area right next to where I live. The workers are always super nice. I highly recommend this place.
The food is delicious!

One of the best Filipino-American restaurants I’ve been to! My family and I went for brunch which was absolutely delicious! Purple Patch has done an amazing job fusing Filipino and American breakfast! Every plate had its own unique twist but still had that home-cooked Filipino taste to it. Most importanty, the price point for each dish is affordable and reasonable with the portion especially for brunch in the DC area. Chef and owner Patrice Cleary also made our visit memorable by stopping by our table and personally greeted us. Patrice and Purple Patch made my husband’s birthday brunch a tasty and memorable dining experience that we will surely cherish! We can’t wait to be back!

In addition to excellent food, Purple Patch goes above and beyond with customer service.  I put in an order through Door Dash that the driver didn't pick up, and then somehow the driver canceled my order.  The Purple Patch manager personally delivered my order to me when Door Dash dropped the ball.  This was such a class act.  I will certainly continue to be a loyal customer.

I was here last night because I wanted my girlfriend to experience Filipino food as I am of the same ethnicity. I ordered a bunch of entrees from Sinigang to Laing to Bicol Express and Bulalo. Three of four dishes were amazing, they got the right spice for the Bicol Express, the right sour taste with the Sinigang and that Filipino taste with Laing but the Bulalo threw me off. I have been raised in the Philippines and Bulalo usually consists off bone marrow,potatoes,corn,vegetables and of sort. The one served for me was ONE piece of short rib, vegetables but without the corn and potatoes, and dumplings. I have never seen dumplings in Bulalo and it wasn't even on the menu. The menu stated that it has a bone marrow and the rest. I made it clear with the server and manager that this is not Bulalo and most certainly is not worth $20. Server and manager told me they will remake the dish but ultimately gave me just corn and potatoes. I didn't say the taste was bad but if I order Bulalo, I expect to be served Bulalo. The manager was nice enough to give us complimentary desserts. If you are a Filipino or a Filipino food enthusiast, this is not a place for you. I gave it 3 out 5 because the other dishes were okay, it's just I take pride of our dishes because I cook them to at home and the owner is Filipino. Thank you.

This might not be as authentic as I would prefer filipino food to be, but it's extremely good and flavourful, preparations are well, love the place.  Legit comfort food and prepared wonderfully.  Only outside seating. Our server Ms. Nancy was great and friendly.  Definitely will come back

First let me say, coming from a Filipino background I know first hand authentic Filipino food. A couple of friends told me about this place & I decided to try it. First off the lumpia, which is one of the most popular & my personals favorite finger food. I was disappointed! It tasted fake as if it were store bought, the meat looked & chewed like rubber. It didn’t taste fresh at all.I also ordered the chicken adobo(which is another favorite) & I was also disappointed. My friend ordered Tocino & garlic rice. We both enjoyed the rice. The tocino was a little burnt, but was still eatable. We also ordered sinigang. I can honestly say, that was the best dish (As a whole) that was delicious. Cooked great seasoned well. The vegetables were delicious.

Great outdoor seating. Food was ok. Seafood options are better. Dont order the sizzling sisig. Smells really good but the taste is nowhere near authentic, its more catered to the American palate. Desserts are ok to good. The Ube cheesecake was the best.  Service was amazing. Kudos to the staff accommodating our small birthday get together during this pandemic time. They do a great job observing COVID-19 precautions.  I would recommend to those new to Filipino cuisine.

Really cute vibe with excellent customer service. Came here for a date night and we had the lechon kawali (so crispy with just the right amount of fat), hot apple cider (delicious), and the coconut-braised short rib adobo from their daily specials menu (this was EXCELLENT. Everything from the sauce to the meat–the most tender short rib I've ever had–to the perfect serving portion). I really hope they add this adobo dish to the main dinner menu because once my friends and family can come visit safely, I am taking them all here.
Must try their dessert menu!
We went for the sixth time this evening and they did not disappoint, as usual. Our favorite dishes so far are the Red Snapper, Calamansi Tofu, and Ube Pie.

Purple Patch has exquisite service and food! They’re one of my favorite spots in DC for outdoor dining. They have a great patio with covered awnings. They also have great vegan options. I love their Calamansi Towka: fried tofu and pineapple fried rice. I highly recommend going to Purple Patch. It’s a woman owned business too :)
The Purple Patch very generously donated food to poll workers at the Marie Reed center. It was absolutely delicious, and kept us going on our 13 hour shift. Definitely recommend the wings!

Solid food and drinks bursting with loads of flavor! Excellent service and a very friendly owner! This spot impressed me 3 years ago and continues to wow me today. During the covid pandemic they offer about 50 covered seats right outside their storefront and have hand sanitizer at each table.  While their vast drink menu lists really thoughtful cocktails, I super recommend their Spicy Calamansi Margarita or Sour with perfect amounts of heat and strength! Then to start, Mama Alice's Lumpia arrives piping hot with a real delish and downhome taste filled with tender pork/beef in a crispy wrapper with a lovely banana ketchup sauce. Then their sweet and spicy Calamansi Wings are a real winner!  From their brunch menu, their savory Sizzling Sisig stopped the show with a smokey/steamy presentation of very tasty pork belly and shoulder with onion, vinegar, bird's eye chili, and lemon juice topped with a fried egg and a side of garlic fried rice. I actually finished the entire plate! Then my friends ordered their Eggplant Adobo Bowl and their Ube Waffles w/Filipino fried chicken and Ube Ice Cream and were both completely blown away!  During my previous visit, I thoroughly inhaled their Purple Patch Sliders and I'm sure they're still incomparable. With 2 exceptional experiences at brunch and dinner years apart, I recommend this spot as a must!  NOTES/TIPS: **Restroom down the stairs all the way in the back to the left. Diaper changing table and diapers available. All still available during the covid pandemic. **They charge your credit card table side. **Filipino snacks available upstairs even during the covid pandemic. **Female Veteran-owned

Love this place! The food is always delicious..We live in the area so we are there at least once a week..friendly staff.love the adjustment during covidt. Support these businesses they deserve to stay open.  Blessings to your entire team..

Purple Patch has some really great food, but even better service. We ordered food through Caviar (Door Dash), who messed up our order by not including 2 items at delivery. The owner of Purple Patch fired up our missing items and personally delivered them with some yummy extras to our hotel! This is great service from a great restaurant! Many thanks for a great experience!
Just fenomenal got that red snapper. Friendly staff, fast, drinks was just perfect.
Very friendly service and great food. Plenty of outdoor seating in a safe environment.
The service was great. The food was bland. Had the Chicken Adobo which had no taste. The presentation seemed odd and made it hard to eat.
Tasty, and large portions
Great food!
Purple Patch has adapted really well to COVID-19! They now have a fun little market to look through and see food and baked goods and drinks as you pick up your food.
Nice spread tables outside,  great waiter and good food!!

We enjoy to go out. Last night we came to this magnificent place which we didn’t know before. We passed a beautiful experience there with delicious dishes and an efficient crew and a distinguished chief cook. We put this restaurant in our list  and we will surely come back very soon.  Highly recommended.

This restaurant is my favored. I visit a lot of restaurants but here I  constantly return again and again. The team is very helpful and the cuisine they cook is so flavorful. I never decline to have a nice dinner in this place. I recommend this place with pleasure.
I like this venue a lot. there is a unique mood. The food is wonderful. the service is dynamic and the personel is trained. The price is decent. I warmly recommend.

Actually 2.5 stars. Please read the front of the drink menu, they charge 20% tip automatically. Not a really good example of Filipino cuisine, well at least the items we picked. All I tasted in the Bistek was jarred garlic and salt, the steak was chewy. The chicken was close to burnt, the rice was under cooked, and the eggplant cooked in coconut milk was way to sweet for me. Very expensive for what you received. We sat outside. Staff were wearing mask's and our server did a nice job.

I took my sis here for her birthday and it was wonderful! The owner prepped our table beforehand, and she came out to spend time with us at the end of our meal. The staff was so kind. And the food was DELICIOUS. It was wonderful to finally eat properly made lumpia at a restaurant. The pancit bihon was also on point and fresh. Highly recommend!
I love this place!!!this is always go to for our family celebrations! Great service and I love the food
They serve big portions and for reasonable pricing. helpful staff members. Keep it up.
Great Filipino-inspired food as always. Patio seating is open with many tables outside. Will charge an automatic 20% gratuity at the end.

I recently ordered pickup from this great spot in Columbia Heights! Staff is friendly, service is fast, food is great. We got the Lechon, eggplant hash, ube pancakes, and halo halo. The latter two were my favorite, and I want to go back for the Laing and calamansi wings which come highly recommended from a friend. They also have some grab and go/market items available. Please support this great local business!

We enjoy going out. Yesterday we  found this magnificent restaurant which we didn’t know before. We passed a beautiful evening there with very good food and  an experienced crew and  a professional chief cook. We  added this restaurant in our list  and we will certainly go again very soon. We warmly recommend.
Delicious food, great social distancing measures!
I like this place very much. there is a different mood. The meals are tasty. the service is dynamic and the stuff is professional. The cost is satisfactory. truly recommend.
Wow! Ordered through Caviar at the food arrived in under 30 minutes. Everything we ordered was delicious, and I regret not getting more dishes to try!
The owner was rather inconsiderate of a me a few years ago, so I stopped going here.
I admire this place very much. It has a unique feeling. The kitcen is marvelous. the service is dynamic and the crew is polite. The pay is honest. extremely recommend.
Bicol Express was FANTASTIC

At the first moment  you arrive in that restaurant  the stuff gives you a nice feeling. Very hospitable stuff, it is a good restaurant to  pass time with friends or with your date. enjoyable  cooking, professional  chef de cuisine, decent  pay and generous  service. Highly recommended.
Delicious! Get the escabeche and the tamarind collins!

Everything we ordered was delicious, the atmosphere was so cozy, and the service was good. My favorites were the Lechon Kawali, Ginataang Alimasag & Spinach, Pancit Bihon (ordered with shiitakes), and Ube bread pudding and ice cream. Would definitely recommend.
My first visit. Everything was great
Loved it. Great food
Sizzling Sisig is amazing and the cocktails are great! Always love the lumpia and the brussel sprouts.
Awesome food and service in a wonderfully cozy space!
Good place to eat Filipino foo, the service was good and fast
👍 great
Delicious

Food is not bad but the cost to taste ratio is way too high. Got the pork sisig and some lumpia. $18 for dry, overlysalty yet under seasoned pork (there is more to life than just throw more salt on the food). $1.60 each for lumpia that taste like frozen potstickers.  You'd probably like this place if you're someone who doesn't mind overpaying for food to show how cultured you are. If you want actual good food for a respectable price, find your nearest Mexican place instead.  Service is good

This restaurant is the one I like best. I visit plenty of restaurants but here I  constantly return again and again. The team is very amicable and the cooking they offer is so delicious. I am always happy to have a nice meal in this place. I recommend this place with pleasure.

Had a wonderful brunch here! The space is very cute, and having your name on your waiting table is a nice touch! The food was delicious, and the service was great. I got the chicken and waffles which was very good; the chicken was cooked perfectly and the ice cream is a great touch. My dining partner got the tofu hash; the tofu was good but the garlic rice was better. We plan to come back for dinner!
Amazing spot for some great filipino food - each course was exceptional, but I think my favorite part was the ube brownie and ice cream!
Amazing food and service.
The food was fantastic. And the ambiance feels like you're eating in a speakeasy. Who knew Ube as a dessert would be so delicious!
Had a good experience in this spot with my girlfriend. The food comes quick and the service is just excellent. Prices are convenient.
This place never fails to deliver. They have fantastic food for reasonable prices, there no long wait even when the spot is full.
Worth a try. See if you like it for yourself.
Best waffle I've ever had

The food was a amazing, brought a friend who grew up eatting fillipino and he was brought back to days of old, especially when it came to dessert and the halo-halo.  Our only regret was that the hot sauce was more like a soy sauce.  The food itself and and the service were amazing.  Restaurant was busy but not over packed.  Seated right away and enjoyed a hidden gem I'm gonna have to go back to, as there is still a lot more menu to explore.
I love the menu ... the location ... and the atmosphere here.
Made my stomach happy.
I constantly stop purchasing some food here. I liked the speedy service and well cooked food. Keep up the good work.
this is my favorite place in dc. definitely get the calamansi wings (this is the only place I crave wings from) and lumpia and save room for ube everything for dessert.
My first time! Marvelous atmosphere for an acoustic musical experience.
The brunch menu was great! Had the filipino-american breakfast
This restaurant provides amazing service and enjoyable menu. The best place around here. The food served fast and the prices are affordable. Will definitely recommend this place.

Make sure to make reservations for dinner. Any of their pork belly dishes are great as well as anything adobo. The escabeche is amazing though and is my top recommendation! All of their drinks are also very tasty and even non-alcoholic drinks can have some added. The vibe is very boho and very well decorated and cozy. Service was excellent and very attentive. Very excited to try brunch one day!

This is authentic Filipino food. The lechon is bursting with flavor. Lots of great dishes on the menu. I had the Bicol Express, which is pork belly in a shrimp-paste coconut milk soup. Great cocktails, friendly staff and cool vibe inside the restaurant. Happy to spread the word about a great DC restaurant.
Top notch service and warm atmosphere.
Oh my....what a treat..lechon kawali , mango salad, fried spicy wings....yummmyyyyy
Great food and atmosphere and will definitely go again!

Friendly atmosphere and good food.  I am of the age now where everyone who visits has kids.  Luckily, Purple Patch allows us to give them a very good example of the DC brunch scene in a very kid-friendly atmosphere.

One of the few Filipino restaurants in DC. Unless you're looking for grab-and-go style Filipino food, Purple Patch is your go-to Filipino restaurant (with the price tag to accompany it). Ordered pork sinigang with rice and a rye calamansi sour. Patis on the side!  Not pictured: the amazing ube bread pudding with ube ice cream. Don't sleep on their dessert menu!
Really good, Danny is a great server.
Love the Americanization of Filipino food. Well done!!!!!

Lots of places serve great food but the passion and personality of owner/chef Patrice and her staff is what makes this place special.  We were greeted warmly when we came in and made to feel special the entire evening.  Patrice's love of cooking and love for her culture is evident.
Owner is GREAT. Food was AWESOME. Worth it. Exceeded my expectation. Food is REAL FILIPINO experience. Really recommendable. Thank you for the GREAT B-Day EXPERIENCE Chef Patrice💞

I normally don't leave reviews but this restaurant deserves one-- excellent service, excellent tasting foods, and perfect drinks. Could not ask for anything more to my standards they were way up there might have surpassed them.

The food here is AMAZING. We ordered several things, not one was bad, or even just ok. My favorite was the crab fried rice with fried egg and Ube bread pudding. The service was great and the ambiance was nice (intimate, even for a weekend in the city). This place is a must try if you're in the area.
Honestly, very delicious and impeccable service.

Went here last night with 2 friends and had a great time!  Great space.  The food and craft cocktails were excellent and Bridgette and Zack at the bar took excellent care of us.  Thanks you two!  We will definitely be back.
Their recently redesigned menu offers a few more vegetarian options, but you should just get the eggplant adobo every time. Really tasty deserts too.
Fantastic and fresh food, I liked the mood this place has, and the workers were welcoming. I will surely eat here again.

Incredible! The family style feast was amazing. First time eating Filipino food, but the service experience and hospitality was out of this world. The flavors are amazing. I can't say enough good things.
Place is great. Good locations. Super sexy restaurant. The design is beautiful. It’s comfy and artistic. Their coffees are great too.
Amazing food! So incredibly tasty. Great vegetarian options plus creative, delicious drinks. Nice vibe too. Go!
They added a nice touch - if you reserve s table, there is a printed card with your name welcoming you.
Awesome place, order anything with ube!
The food that I ate was really good and the service was geat
Food was delicious.
The food was yum. Pleasant waitress. Great  seating area with comfy chairs!
Because it is yummy and we'll priced for the DC area considering the quality and portion sizes
Great food, good service. Will go again.

Visited all the way from Toronto since we were heading South and decided to stop by this charming Filipino resto - definitely worth it! The food was delicious, the staff and service was great, and ambiance was popping. Albeit, it was a bit noisy, and the place seemed cramped, but overall my experience was awesome and I would highly recommend the ube bread pudding as well as the lumpia, and the sizzling sisig dish.
Unbelievable. Great food well priced and amazing service.

Could not be more pleased with Purple Patch, one of the few places in DC where you can always get ube ice cream. Solid lumpia, and the taro dish was really good too. Good spot for a drink/date/family dinner.
True Mt Pleasant gem! Out of this world cocktails, stellar Filipino food and some of the best bartenders in the District. Happy Hour until 8pm and try the sizzling sisig 😁
Friendly staff, quick seating, amazing atmosphere for all groups and great food!!!
Excellent Filipino food. Fast and friendly service. Reasonably priced. Will definitely be back.
Maybe it's because we ordered mostly vegetarian - maybe meat dishes are much better here - but we were super disappointed with the quality and lack of imagination in the dishes we ordered.
One of my favorite neighborhood spots! The chicken adobo and ube ice cream are highlights.
One of my favorite spots to grab something to eat. good location, clean, and good service. Very good job!
Banging, if you haven't been yet you should remedy that situation fast. Killer good food.

I read amazing reviews about Purple Patch, and definitely wanted to check it out! I went here for brunch on a Saturday morning; unfortunately, the experience was a letdown with the food I ordered. I ordered the Waffle with Ube Ice Cream and Filipino Fried Chicken as my entree, and Bread Pudding with Ube Ice Cream as my dessert.  The good: The restaurant itself is a small area located upstairs, and it is nicely decorated. If you make reservations, they print out your name on a card, which is a nice touch. The ube ice cream is delicious! Has a strong delicious flavor, and I would eat a pint of this if offered. The waffle was warm and soft. I would enjoy the entree, except for one issue: the chicken.  The bad: The chicken was very dry for being dark meat. You're given 2 pieces of dark meat, and I was hoping for it to be moist and tender, but it was dry all over. I really wish I could have enjoyed the dish, but the chicken ruined the experience.  Overall, I'll come here again to check out their other food since there aren't too many delicious Filipino restaurants that are mentioned in the Michelin Guide. The banana bread with ube ice cream is delicious! However, I would order only ube ice cream because it is my favorite part!
Purple Patch is my favorite Filipino restaurant in DC. The food and service are always great! Recommend both brunch and dinner.
Great Philipino restaurant in a hidden location...
Loved the ambience and the food!!
This place has a really good value and very delicious Filipino food!
Best Filipino food in DC!
Been here twice. Chef came out to talk to us. Shes awesome
AMAZING!!! Laing with chicken is amazing!

Never had Filipino food and was not disappointed! Had the Tacino dish (the spelling could be off), which included a fresh house and papaya salad. I am not a huge pork fan, but this was super delicious. Also, I recommend getting the Ube bread pudding dessert. You will not be disappointed!

Good traditional Asian cuisine is seldom found in the DMV, let alone true Southeast Asian cooking. We came to Purple Patch to celebrate my friends birthday, and had a Kamayan with all the best dishes: escabeche, laing, bistek, sisig, all the adobo's, and so much more.  You know it's the real deal when the the fish, lumpia, and eggplant are on point!  The real mark of amazing, is when a meal brings you back to a special time in your life, when you enjoyed a delicious home-cooked feast, and shared endless stories with your loved ones. Tonight was an extremely rare occasion, in which I got to re-experience my childhood. I have Patrice and the entire staff at Purple Patch to thank for this exquisite treat. 🙏

Made reservations on a Saturday for their famous Kamayan meal to celebrate my birthday. So glad I did! My guests were pleased and kept thanking me for organizing the event and absolutely loved the food. Chef Patrice set up the food and educated us on each dish and her overall story. She’s so passionate and we loved and hung onto every word she said.  If you haven’t tried a Kamayan meal, book it! Reservations are required and it’s super easy.  We will be back to try their brunch!
The adopoo dishes and the other soup dishes were extremely sour. Purple yam ice cream was just taro ice cream. Yam and taro are really different things. Service was fine.
Amazing food and drinks. Wonderful, friendly, community vibes. I had my first TWO purple beers. The local DC Brau is pictured. I would take my friends here for a genuine night out. Absolutely love.
Filipino food, yum! Appetizer, brunch, and dessert! 99% as good as my mom's. Great service and recommendations by our server.

This restaurant exceeded our expectations - both service and food. Our server was very accommodating and understanding of our food allergies. We had a reservation for 13 people so it was not an easy job, but all was well. Found out there are many vegan and vegetarian options. I really enjoyed the calamansi tokwa (tofu and pineapple fried rice) and the calamansi juice is delicious. The ube cupcake and ice cream were wonderful as well. My first visit to the restaurant was not so great, but I'm glad I came back.
There's so much room on the bottom floor! Great selection of food and drink and a really nice ambience with low lighting. Service was fast and super friendly; excited for another trip here!
First time in the restaurant and wow, blew my mind. Came in with high expectations, and they surpassed them.
Terrific food and brilliant service
Tasty and swanky spot

We went for brunch to celebrate my mom's 50th birthday. We had a moderate sized party that changed to a larger party of 19. They were so great at accommodating us with the changes. I didn't find out until we were waiting for them to open that out party size dropped. When we told them after they had already set up the table, it was no issue. The absolute best part of the Purple Patch was the hospitality. From second I emailed about the reservation to everyone that visited the table. Everyone's attitude was stellar. It really was like we were at an aunt's house because we were at ease. They were slammed and the bit of the wait at the table didn't bother anyone due to the vibe of the restaurant.  The mix up of the food for the Filipino/American Brunch was really innovative and fun. I haven't been to any other Filipino restaurant where they mixed it up like they did at the Purple Patch. Out of our party of 14, the favorites of the table were:  Mama Alice's Lumpia (now you know your mom's is always the best, but these were the closest to my mom's) Ube Pancakes & Macapuno Syrup +Lechon Kewali (the pancake was different, but the the lechon was the best. I was so juicy and tender. If you don't get this meal, order a side of the lechon) Ube Bread Pudding w/ Ube Ice Cream (out of this world good. No nuts in it (for those with allergies) they make everything in this in house. We should have ordered more for the table.) Halo Halo (Just a classic with a twist. Delish)  We had two toddlers there and they have an area by the restrooms with lots of toys that is semi closed in. It was a nice touch. The booster seats attach to the tall chairs and the children's menu were great. The fruit bowl was a great mixture of fresh fruit. All this to say that it is child friendly place.

2nd time here it didnt disappoint. Filipino Restaurant week but decided to order ala carte anyway so we can taste more variety for the same price. This meal was more memorable than the first I think. Delicious!  If they cut up the pork smaller the Sisig dish would be perfect!

Never had Fillapino food before but I really enjoyed the food here. A cozy restaurant that was very Welcoming to my Family. We stopped here after reading positive reviews and We were staying at a Hotel near by. I would like to go try more next time I am in DC. My son loves the French Toast and Pork, I had marinated Steak, my Husband had flavorful chicken adobo. Very cool experience.
Good food and nice atomosphere.
Excellent play between local favorites and Filipino fare. The sizzling pork with raw egg was excellent. I can't wait to come back for the dinner mwnu.!!
There are places that can get the act together for Mother’s Day, and there are places that can’t. This place can’t.
Fantastic service and authentic Filipino cuisine!
Don't understand the rave reviews.
The Adobo pork belly and Bistek was amazing! The lumpia is some of the best I’ve had and I have a Filipino grandmother! Highly recommended, 10/10 will eat there again.

🚨PSA 🚨  Let me tell you about these ube pancakes.  I could write a sonnet  for these flawlessly delicious  pancakes that delighted my stomach. Ube flavored deserts hold a special place in my heart as my Nai frequently made them growing up (halaya & roll cakes, I still daydream about you).  Overjoyed to find out I could get a taste of these here in DC, I went to  brunch with my partner to try these sinful cakes. The texture and taste was perfection; soft pillowy lavender stacks with an understated sweetness, lightly drizzled in macapuno syrup. The amount of pancakes provided was filling and left me thoroughly satiated...but ah, it was over all too soon.  Objectively speaking,  these are best pancakes to grace the entirety of my existence. I will be back, most likely settled in the corner of the restaurant gleefully ugly sobbing at our tasteful reunion. Try the cakes, please!
Great Filipino food fusion!
It's ok do not expect it to be authentic. It's more watered down to suite normal American pallets.

If you're looking for good Filipino food then come here. Make sure you gave a reservation or come to the restaurant early or else you'll be waiting a long time for a table. I recommend getting Biko for dessert! I had their tocilog (grilled pork) for breakfast (see picture) and it was good!

I've only been here for brunch but I was extremely impressed. The diverse offerings are all equally delicious. Nothing that I samples from my own plate or others at my table disappointed. The vibe upstairs is bright and airy with a more bar like restaurant downstairs.
The purlple patch is a classic , I enjoy coming here. They have really good Filipino food. My favorite is the chicken adobo.

This place is so amazing, I can eat to 110% fullness here. I love Filipino food, and Purple Patch really hits it out of the park. The lumpia, rice, sisig, pancit, adobo, and more are so amazing. I would eat everything on their menu if I could. Even their desserts are a must. I've been here for both a Kamayan and a regular dinner date. The staff are great, and they love to see their food enjoyed.
My husband got the Chicken Adobo it was cold but still taste amazing. The French toast and pork were AMAZING!  Definitely coming back
Loved their drinks and adobo wings

I wouldn't say it's just like mom makes, cuz it isn't. The adobo could be more tender, the lumpia a little more flavorful.  I wonder if the banana ketchup is from scratch?  All that said, Filipino food offerings are kind of few and far between and this is a welcome addition to the restaurant scene. I'll come back, but this doesn't match homecooking for me.

I'm not sure what the hype is about but I unfortunately couldn't bring myself to like any of the dishes here. The high rating really surprises me! My girlfriends and I ordered a variety of all the dishes and they were all overly salted, unpleasantly sour, or unforgivably bland. Even the lumpia was a disappointment - so soggy. I don't plan on returning.
Awesome food and a solid happy hour
Filipino food with a twist. Delicious and reasonable price point. Family get together is better down in main floor. Basement has bar and can be noisy. Overall, great food and location.
Can't wait to visit again. Such an interesting place to say the least. I wanna visit on game night.
Food is really good. Wines a bit overpriced.

Was really looking forward to going to Purple Patch, but my experience was lackluster. Food was good, but didn't stand out. I was also a little surprised by the service (which wasn't poor, but wasn't attentive.) Plenty of better options for the same price point.
Good food, great hospitality, an amazing story. Definitely get the eggplant and pork belly

I really wanted to love Purple Patch but after going 3 times, I've decided it just isn't worth the price point. If you have any control over it, do not sit downstairs. It smells like very strong bathroom cleaner and really ruins the meal. The smaller upstairs area is much cuter and ambient.
Wow!  Great food and service.
Great place to visit when in DC. Great service and good ambience. Tried the Escabeche, presented really well and tasted good. Ube Ice cream is a must try!
Delicious!
Pretty busy spot even on a Monday night. Taste was spot on, though I felt the amount of crab in the crab dishes was disappointing.
I absolutely love this place. The food is amazing, atmosphere perfect and the staff friendly and helpful.
Came in with an appetite left fulfilled. Great food and service.

Amazing brunch spot that has no fewer than 8 options that all looked amazing. I got a hash with chicken and every bite was a culinary rollercoaster of euphoria. The meat was perfectly cooked and the garlic rice reverberated around my tastebuds like gas particles being heated up in an flask. The restaurant itself has very friendly staff and the oddest collection of movies going on.

We were here for dinner date night with my boyfriend, and the ambience was so cozy and the food was great. We had one vegan and the fish entree , and we enjoyed it both. Over all our stay was  awesome. Great food!! Highly recommend!!
The bartender Scott was extremely helpful, and suggested Fernet for the crippling hangover I was nursing.  Between that and the fried pork belly, my Saturday was saved.

Awesome little place. Although it's quite spacious once inside. Plenty of TVs... at least 7 screens. Food is fantastic on any level but especially for a neighborhood spot. A real gem that Mt. Pleasant can be proud of.

Came here in a snowstorm and it was the best decision I made while visiting DC. The food is interesting, well made, with amazing flavor. The bartender was a sweetheart and made some great recommendations. I can imagine it gets a lot more crowded when the weather is nice but I would definitely recommend and would go again!!
5 stars for food and cozy setting and friendly staff but the coffee was bland

Great pinoy food with excellent service! Halo-halo was superb and the restaurant is completely nut-free which is amazing for any nut-allergic kids. Sisig, lumpia and lechon were all excellent as well. Will go back again when we are in the DC area.

This would have been a 5-star rating... The food is exceptional and fairly priced. The service, in general is lovely. A Filipino friend recommended this place, and with two friends we went together. We were blown away by the excellent food. The four of us each ordered 2 drinks, an entree, and dessert. At the end of the meal, just as we recieved the check from our server (who was in no way a problem) we were very rudely told by the host that we must leave quickly as the table was needed for another seating. There was no apology, no gentle ask if we wouldn't mind, no attempt at politeness. He didn't even bother to observe that we had just signed our checks and he could have waited another 2-3 minutes till we left on our own. It was 5 till the hour... not even at the hour that the table would have been scheduled. He immediately began calling servers over to begin bussing our table, and even took our glasses away while we sat there stunned at how absurdly rude the host was. Just before this moment, we had been happy and speaking with each other how wonderful everything was. The rudeness ruined every last bit of that warm and glowing feeling. The manager, who we immediately asked our server to bring, looked horrified when I shared what had just happened, but she offered no apology for how we had been treated. Her response was strange.  If you come here, don't expect a pleasant experience. It, too, could be ruined in the very last moments of your visit. The food was good, but not worth the strange and rude treatment from staff.
Delicious food. Great atmosphere. Everything we had was incredibly tasty. Will definitely will be returning.
Great food, beer, and atmosphere
Definitely try the walnut old fashioned and the myriad of Ube desserts

The big negative thing I have to say is the price. It's up there but Try it out !  It is some what Americanized but enough to still be Pillipinothe. The wait staff is excellent.  I suggest Brunch should be the 1st visit. The Top Singlong is delecious.
awesome food here
Food was Amazing and the staff was Phenomenal!!

I’m Filipino, and I was honestly disappointed. If you’re looking for classic Filipino food then don’t come here. Purple patch takes many liberties in trying to modernize filipino cuisine but completely misses the mark.  We ordered ginisang hipon ( sautéed shrimp) but was served in a broth, not only that, it only included approx 5 pieces of shrimp. That’s over $3 per shrimp!! Admittedly, the flavor was nice but way overpriced for a dish.  The bistek was meh.

It's a great place. I usually go there for trivia on Monday nights at 8pm. They have happy hour going before it starts and then some trivia night dinner/drink specials. The food is good and fairly priced. But there is no vegetarian option for trivia night specials. Great place to hang out with some friends. The staff is super friendly as well and will chat it up with you!
Best bloody Mary

We had a wonderful experience at this restaurant. Everything, the food, the service, the noise level were perfect. The chef even visited our table and helped us select our entrees. I can't wait to go back.

Recently went to DC for a conference and discovered this gem. O M G . The food was amazing. We shared 4 different plates amongst us. The staff was friendly and welcoming. If you are in the DC area def check this place out.
Brought my family in for my anniversary. Food was amazing. The Turon was a perfect ending to a great meal. Service was equally matched to the food.
Its was awsome
Very decent bar with a  neighborhood feel. I will say, however, Filipino food is not in itself a cosmopolitan culinary experience. Not done quite right -- not for everyone
Great food, great service, interesting atomsphere

The sinigang - is not sour and has potatoes.. So it seemed like it's nilaga  Adobo - it was okay a little too salty  Lechon Kawali was really good.. We eat it with rice here in 🇵🇭 but there it's an appetizer but still yummy  Note make a booking so u get the seat upstairs.. Place looks quaint and cozy.
The bartender Scott was extremely helpful, and suggested Fernet for the crippling hangover I was nursing.  Between that and the fried pork belly, my Saturday was saved.
Food was good but dessert was even better!

I loved the eggplant dish that we got here. Honestly pretty amazing. The fish dish was also good. Cool atmosphere and of course the yummy purple desserts! I think they even have live piano sometimes here. I’d definitely come again.
The food is amazing, customer service is great and the atmosphere is perfect.
Nice and cozy.  Best to call ahead and reserve a table. Try the Ginger Pork Belly over Cantonese noodles.
Good food and nice ambience

I can't say enough good things about Purple Patch. The food is magnificent; extremely tasty and reasonably priced. The best brunch in Mt. Pleasant - try the Sizzling Sisig or Chicken and Waffles with Purple Ube ice cream. Cocktails are inventive and frequently change. The service has never been anything short of excellent, and the owner frequently has come around to chat and make sure we like everything. Reservations get a nice welcome card, which is a nice touch. Trivia on Mondays is great - and hard!
Warm welcoming place with great food!

I’ve had the the pleasure of being introduced to Purple Patch by a good friend... Purple Patch is an awesome authentic Philippine restaurant! We had the pleasure of a family style dinner, we enjoyed San Miguel, Mama Alices’ Lumpia & Atchara Papaya Salad as our appetizer. The Papaya salad yummmm new favorite especially since I learned its fermented papaya 😋 as Our main course we shared the Ginisang Hipon, Pancit Canton, and Laing! My personal favorite was the Pancit Canton, the table’s favorite was the Laing. For desert we shared   Ube Bread Pudding w/ Ube Ice Cream 😋 ...the food was so delicious I ordered 2 meals to go for my family, they enjoyed the crispy egg plant and the Alimasag Fried Rice which were both very tasty! This was the first time my mum had lump crab fried rice and she loves crab 😋 definitely coming back to enjoy more meals including the desserts... the red snapper looks amazing as so does the Turon... I will be trying those next... be sure to make a reservation, the place is very popular

This is one of those places you need to come back to many times so you can try everything on the menu. It's all delicious and it's all relatively affordable. Bonus, if you go to the bar between 5-8 Monday-Friday, beers are half off, and they have a good beer selection! We're talking $3.50 for Bell's Two Hearted good. Helpful hint: if you can't decide, go for the fish at the top of the menu or the adobo chicken!
Great place

The food was decent but it is not authentic Filipino food. Adobo does not have vegetables in it and sinigang is not supposed to use lemon broth. The flavors for the entrees were mediocre compared to what real Filipino food is supposed to be. The best part of the meal was dessert.

We were sweaty from walking around Rock Creek Park so we sat downstairs in the bar area.  The bartender was super friendly. I got a ginger lemon mimosa and my partner got the Bloody Mary with Bloody Mary vodka that they make in house. We split ube pancakes with fried chicken and ube ice cream.  Everything was so good, will definitely was back.
Good Filipino food
Ube ice cream, lumpia and amazing bloody Marys.....among other delicious food and drink!

Amazing does not begin to describe the experience, culture, and delicious food this place has to offer.  It is a unique dining experience full of flavor and beautiful atmosphere and wonderful staff.  I drove from Hanover, PA for this experience and it was well worth it.
Drinks were very good.  Loved the spring rolls.  We got the "bistek," which was ok.  In retrospect, we wish we got something more authentic.  Dessert was very good.  Service was great.
Our group had a wonderful time!  The was great and Patrice is a brilliant host!
Great food and music!
Good food, good service !
Americanized Filipino food. I found it delicious but my Filipino friends said it really was not up to what they expected.
Very nice place to eat..foods delicious coming from the Philippines we know right away if the foods served are good,  and this is one of the best places we've been too. Highly recommended..
Amazing food!! The owner Patrice is so sweet!! Loooooved the crab fried rice... Def want to try the fried fish next time!

Best Filipino food this side of the Pacific! Cool, modern vibe without being "trendy". The biggest recommendation I can make is the Ube bread pudding. Incredible! Would also highly recommend the Sisig, Ube pancakes (check for availability), bbq skewers, and Crispy Eggplant Adobo. Purple Patch also boasts one of the warmest owners/hosts I have had the pleasure of meeting. Patricia Cleary is a large part of what makes Purple Patch a priority on any traveller's or foodie's must see list. Really warm and friendly AND is a former Marine!!!
Great food, service, and atmosphere
Some of the best Filipino food in DC and Maryland. Highly recommend. Menu is well explained for those who have never eaten Filipino before.

Place is nice. 1. It just takes a while to get your orders or even ask for a waitress to take your orders.. Maybe it's busy but food comes fast.  2. Lechon kawali is really good so yummy it's an appetizer here  3. Pork sinigang - it's different.. It only has potatoes and some kale I think. It's not as sour and doesn't have the usual sinigang veggies like eggplant and string beans. It kind of taste like nilaga. Not sure but the pork has this old meat taste like maybe too frozen before cooked?  4. Chicken adobo is okay its not the dry chicken it's saucy. It's okay  5. Leche flan is I guess ok but I think they used egg whites for it coz the texture and taste is different from the original or creamy Leche flans.  6. Staff are pleasant and nice. The owners are there and nice Ms Alice would say hi to the guest she's a lovely woman.

The Americans enjoyed their food, but the Filipinos didn't.  We also got there a little late for brunch and they were rushing us so much to get an order in that I didn't even get a chance to sit down until after I ordered.  This place was highly recommended by our Filipino friends, but the Adobo, a Filipino staple dish, was barely edible.  I did enjoy my Tapa and my friend enjoyed their version of locks and bagels.  Maybe I will try them again for dinner, but not brunch.
Everything was so delicious. A real treat for great Filipino food.
Amazing place to do a Kamayan style family dinner.
I like the pork sisig. Fresh and delicious.
I came here for the sizzling sisig and was not disappointed. Best Pinoy food I've had besides my momma's kitchen.
UberEats Contractor Review: Had a long wait😢I got a ticket cuz they took so long! Staff was nice & friendly
Good food, good cocktails, good date spot. Service is fine here. So are prices.
Delicious food. The garlic rice was fantastic!
The noodle dish I had was tasteless. Luckily, the beer was okay.
Very friendly server and so delicious food
I crave the chicken adobo and garlic fried rice!
Love this spot for carry out or dine in or happy hour or night drinks! It has it all! Try the sisig burrito is a winner!
Excellent place!

Service was great. We got seated early and the waitress was very prompt and attentive.  The food was okay. We got started off with some Lumpia which was served with ketchup instead of the sweet and spicy sauce? Idk why. It wasn't too bad but I'd prefer the sweet and spicy sauce with lumpia.  My chicken adobo hash wasn't super great. The meat actually had this old stale taste for some reason and it was kind of dry so it was hard to finish. The garlic rice wasn't even warm at least. One of us got the sizzling sisig and the meat wasn't minced up small enough. The meat that should've been tender was actually quite dry and bland.  Towards the end our waitress kind of rushed us. We asked to order dessert and she brought us a check instead and left briskly. So all in all, average filipino food and service. Definitely not worth driving to dc for.
Great service, yummy food, and very cute setting! Food came out hot and pretty quickly.
They have good Halo2x
Sort of well hidden treasure located in Mt Pleasant. Great food! Friendly staff!  Will return.
A cute little hidden gem. Definitely much larger than it looks.
Tiny portions, overpriced, if you’re looking to fill up, stay away
Best Philippino food in DC

Great atmosphere and food.  Their brunch was great.  I highly recommend their pork sisig.  I was pleasantly surprised by the inclusion of champorado (a childhood favorite), and ube in mulitple forms!  Their lumpia was okay, and I hope one day they will offer Kare Kare.
Good food.
Great vegetarian/ vegan options. Wonderful staff.
Very yummy 👍
Great vibe, casual with a kick. I loved the food.
Nice
Great experience and great food.  Wonderful, warm atmosphere.  I'll definitely go back next time I'm in town. Patrice was so welcoming - made us feel like family.

One of the best places in DC for brunch. Delicious garlic rice and sweet meat is an unbeatable combination. The chicken hash is amazing and their ube pancakes are great too. Their dinner service features many similar dishes but as an experience pales in comparison.
Delicious, unique and creative approach to classic cuisine!  Beyond the food, it's the owner, Patrice, who adds magic to this place with her hospitality!  Go!

A restaurant's first duty is to have delicious fresh cuisine. That they have covered in spades. The service here is in step with the food and the drinks have a nice take on some of the more exotic fruit juices of the Philippines which was very refreshing since it gives you more than the run of the mill options. But of all the great qualities i could go on about, the thing that makes the place so warm and inviting is the chef and owner Patricia. She touches every table and greets everyone as a old friend. Awesome place from casual to a big friends and family dining. I'd call ahead for reservations for a special occasion as they will take the extra steps to make you feel appreciated.
It's just ok
Absolutely delicious!!

Go.  GO!!! And whatever you do, get dessert.  They had one dessert that had several ingredients including shaved ice the server recommended, and we were told to be sure to stir the ingredients together.  It is one of the most creative and delicious things I've eaten in my life.  The service was exceptional, and all the dishes were thoughtfully done and very tasty.
Great food, great drinks, great service. Hell of a place.
Good was fairly good. Service great
My son, who lives near this filipino restaurant, kept pushing for us to visit (and take him along). Very friendly service with tasty dishes. He did not steer us wrong.
Get the ube bread pudding and ice cream dessert! So yummy!!!

Delicious food and AMAZING desserts! I went there on Feb 1st and we just couldn’t stop eating! The food was so good we kept ordering more! I enjoyed my order of chicken wings and house Caesar salad. But to me, the most unexpected and the most delicious part of the menu was desserts! If you, like me, have a sweet tooth and love sweets from all over the world, you would share my excitement about their desserts quality.
Delicious and quaint.
top notch!
My wife and I tried this after a recommendation from a Co worker and we loved it. Super nice staff and delicious food.
Great local spot.

The food was amazing. I was taken there as a suprise dinner. Looking at the decore and everyone in the restaurant I was not expecting to see Filipino food on the menu. A true shock and very pleasant suprise! We ordered the Lumpia as an appitizer. It was crispy, not as full as authentic lumpia but no complaints here, it was good. For the main meal we had Chicken Adobo and Egg Plant Adobo. The Chicken Adobo was a slight twist on the original but very delicious and the broth was to die for. It made me want to go back home to the Philippines and the San Miguel Beer was the icing on the cake. It was comfort food when i needed it most. I Will be back!
Great lighting, cozy welcome atmsosphere and great food!
Great happy hour and excellent food.
My wife is a Filipina and I really enjoy Filipino food but this place was just okay, nothing too special but maybe I've been spoiled.
Great food
The chef and owner took time to talk with my family and me. Filipino hospitality as its finest with incredible food!
Very good Filipino food.  The staff are friendly and we always get good service.

Spectacular atmosphere even though from the outside it's quite underwhelming, but it's still a great place to stop by for some great Filipino food. The service is absolutely amazing, if you're a first timer they walk you through and there …

Let me tell you since my wife and I have been together we have been looking for a good non-buffet style Filipino restaurant and we have finally found one great food great service and nice not over the top atmosphere.  We really need one in Baltimore.

You'll know by the smell when you walk in that you're going to enjoy the food, but the drinks and wait staff won't leave it there. I love this place both for what they have in offer and for how well they've treated me when I go in for either drinks, dinner, or both. Makes a good date spot if you go upstairs, or a great spot for drinks with friends downstairs.
Best pinoy food you'll find around that isn't home cooked and dranks are always a great addition
Great for trivia, well curated but small beer selection, food can be hit or miss.
Always enjoy happy hour. The fries are addictive.
Great food and variety.
I was having a really important conversation with a friend over dinner and was asked to leave or stand at the bar because we had been at the table for two hours. Poor hospitality.
Well prepared food, very nicely seasoned, authentic food of the Philippines.

We had dinner in Purple Patch yesterday. The restaurant is cozy and easy to locate. The food arrived fast and the server was efficient. The food was OK. The Adobo Radicchio Wrap had too much atchara (pickled papaya) on it that it’s overwhelming in my opinion. The table we were seated to smelled like cleaning product (bleach or sanitizer). I’m not sure if it’s coming from the vent close to our table or on the floor.
Love this place!
Great place to eat
Mouth watering menu
Quaint place with an unusual menu. Food and service was very good.
Waiter was very knowledgeable and kind. Food looked and tasted authentic. Dessert was also a treat.
Decent thai food!
Very flavourful!!! The place looks very nice and cozy. Portions may be somewhat small for the price you pay.
Love it!
Very tasty Filipino food. It rivals my mother-in-laws recipes

Cute place BUT bad food. I was served 2 separate dishes and both were bad. Steak csme out really fast was cold ans tasted like tomatoe paste - that's it. Just tomatoe paste.  Server was nice. They need a new cook.
Amazing Vietnamese fusion. I keep going back and everyone I take loves it.
I like Purple Patch (very chill) but it is kinda annoying when the bartender decides to turn off ALL the TV's and says sports can't be watched (just because). Even if its the playoffs.  #gatekeeper
The sissig
Best Filipino food in town
Food is to die for, must try this place!

Good place to check out at least once if looking for a Flipinio fusion dish fix. Portions are just right, not huge causing you to over eat. It's a two story eatry. Downstairs is the bar and a little darker. Upstairs is the restaurant with more light.

Absolutely love this place. Make it here for happy hour about once a week, and often end up ordering some food. The brussel sprouts and the burgers are keepers.  The service is always wonderful and the bar tenders seem to do a solid job of putting together some pretty cool drinks on the fly.
